# Important Definitions

## Operating System

System software that manages hardware resources and provides services to programs.

## Kernel

The core part of the Operating System that directly communicates with hardware.

## Program

A set of instructions stored on disk.

## Process

A running instance of a program loaded into memory.

## Thread

The smallest unit of execution within a process.

---

# Important Points

- Operating System acts as an interface between the user and hardware.
- Kernel is the core part of the Operating System.
- Applications run in User Mode.
- The Kernel runs in Kernel Mode.
- Programs become processes when executed.
- A process can contain multiple threads.
- The Operating System manages CPU, memory, files, devices, and security.

